{%- comment -%} NEWS {%- endcomment -%}
{%- assign status = "Published" -%}
{%- assign title = "The Beginner's Guide to Website Development" -%}
{%- assign slug = "the-beginners-guide-to-website-development" -%}
{%- assign published_date = "now" | date: "%Y-%m-%d" -%}
{%- assign tag = "WebDev" -%}
{%- assign list_view_text = "What skills do I need as a web developer? The basics of how the Internet and websites work. The basics of HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. Libraries and frameworks, like jQuery, React.js, and Bootstrap. Other programming languages, like Python and Ruby (for back-end web devs only) Git and GitHub." -%}
{%- assign author = "Mark Webber" -%}
{%- assign content = "FOUNDATIONS OF WEB DEVELOPMENT<br>Web development skills can lead you to a flexible career in a variety of industries. Building for the web is limited only to your imagination, so it’s great for those excited by the creative aspects of coding.<br><br><br><br>WHO IS THIS COURSE FOR?<br>Web development is ideal for anyone interested in how humans interact with information. A successful web developer will be someone who identifies as a lifelong learner and is always up for exploring the latest trends and learning the latest techniques.HTML and CSS aren't actually classified as programming languages. And while JavaScript is a programming language, it's really forgiving. So this trio is great to start with if you're feeling intimidated by the idea of coding. It’s great for anyone who wants to use code as a creative skill.
" -%}

{%- for i in (1..3) -%}
